cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a novel exploration strategy for deep reinforcement learning agents, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. The use of neural networks and dropout suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a likely category. The focus on exploration and reinforcement learning suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics) as other possible categories. The use of continuous control tasks and experiments with mujoco benchmark suggest cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible category. Finally, the use of visual inputs in some of the experiments suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a less likely but still possible category.
